magnificent /mæɡˈnɪfɪsənt/

1. ADJ If you say that something or someone is magnificent , you mean that you think they are extremely good, beautiful, or impressive. 出色的; 壮丽的 

例： ...a magnificent country house in wooded grounds. …林地中一座漂亮的村宅。 

2. magnificence N-UNCOUNT 出色; 壮丽 

例： I shall never forget the magnificence of the Swiss mountains and the beauty of the lakes. 我永远也不会忘记瑞士山岳的壮美和湖泊的秀丽。

